    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA331-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu tōḻi iravukkuṟi nērntatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how the confidante granted a night tryst.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA331">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uvarviḷai yuppi ṉuḻāa vuḻava</l>
<l>            roḻukai yumaṇar varupata nōkkik</l>
<l>            kāṉa liṭṭa kāvaṟ kuppaip</l>
<l>            pulavumī ṉuṇaṅkaṟ paṭupu ḷōppi</l>
<l>            maṭanōk kāyamō ṭuṭaṉup pēṟi</l>
<l>            yentai timilitu nuntai timileṉa</l>
<l>            vaḷainīr vēṭṭam pōkiya kiḷaiñar</l>
<l>            tiṇṭimi leṇṇun taṇkaṭaṟ cērppa</l>
<l>            viṉitē teyyavem muṉivi ṉallū</l>
<l>            riṉivariṟ ṟavaṟu millai yeṉaiyatūum</l>
<l>            piṟarpiṟa raṟital yāvatu</l>
<l>            tamartama raṟiyāc cēriyu muṭaittē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent4">O man from the cool coast,</l>
<l>where they count the firm boats</l>
<l rend="indent">of [their] relatives gone to hunt in the curved water,</l>
<l rend="indent2">saying</l>
<l rend="indent">“this [is] my father’s boat, [this is] your father’s boat,” mounting</l>
<l rend="indent">together the salt[-mounts], with companions of innocent look,</l>
<l rend="indent">scaring away the birds coming onto the dryings of reeking fish</l>
<l rend="indent2">in heaps, to be guarded, placed in the seashore grove by</l>
<l rend="indent3">the ploughmen who don’t plough for the brackish ripening salt,</l>
<l rend="indent">looking at the proper time for the salt-merchants with [their]</l>
<l rend="indent3">carts to come,</l>
<l>– pleasing it [is], our unafflicted good village,</l>
<l rend="indent">and if [you] come now</l>
<l rend="indent4">it is not at all a mistake,</l>
<l>and it has quarters where one does not know the other</l>
<l>– how [could there be] knowing all the others,</l>
<l rend="indent4">even to some extent<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">piṟar</term> is repeated here in analogy to <term xml:lang="ta">tamar tamar</term> of the following line. This is hard to translate.</note>?<note place="foot">Syntax is difficult to justify here, even though the sense is fairly clear. I would call this an unmarked and asyndetic insertion.</note></l>
        </lg>
      </div>
